thread.title: David Engel
thread.title_full: Viking Bags reviewed by David Engel

author: David Engel
title: David Engel
text:
I purchased this bag because it seemed it would be a better fit for my 2007 Yamaha VStar 1300 Tourer. I did have to modify the bag a little to raise it up a little otherwise the ignition switch was blocked. The bag seems to be of reasonable quality, however the brass grommets on the bag had green tarnish on them. How long had this bag been sitting around. I just installed the bag, so I will see how it holds up.
The order was processed promptly and arrived on time. Packaging was flimsy and the zip lock bag looked like it had been pulled out of a dumpster.
